  58 def no_rewrite_session_config():
  59   rewriter_config = rewriter_config_pb2.RewriterConfig(
  60       disable_model_pruning=True,
  61       arithmetic_optimization=rewriter_config_pb2.RewriterConfig.OFF,
  62       dependency_optimization=rewriter_config_pb2.RewriterConfig.OFF)
  63   graph_options = config_pb2.GraphOptions(rewrite_options=rewriter_config)
  64   return config_pb2.ConfigProto(graph_options=graph_options)

  67 class _RNNCellForTest(rnn_cell_impl.RNNCell):
  68   """RNN cell for testing."""
  69 
  70   def __init__(self, input_output_size, state_size):
  71     self._input_output_size = input_output_size
  72     self._state_size = state_size
  73     self._w = variables.VariableV1(1.0, dtype=dtypes.float32, name="w")
  74 
  75   @property
  76   def output_size(self):
  77     return self._input_output_size
  78 
  79   @property
  80   def state_size(self):
  81     return self._state_size
  82 
  83   def __call__(self, input_, state, scope=None):
  84     return (math_ops.multiply(self._w, input_), state)

  87 class SessionDebugTestBase(test_util.TensorFlowTestCase):
  88   """Base class for unit tests of tfdbg running with tf.Session."""
  89 
  90   @classmethod
  91   def setUpClass(cls):
  92     if test.is_gpu_available():
  93       cls._expected_partition_graph_count = 2
  94       cls._expected_num_devices = 2
  95       gpu_name = test_util.gpu_device_name()
  96       cls._main_device = "/job:localhost/replica:0/task:0" + gpu_name
  97     else:
  98       cls._expected_partition_graph_count = 1
  99       cls._expected_num_devices = 1
 100       cls._main_device = "/job:localhost/replica:0/task:0/device:CPU:0"
 101 
 102   @classmethod
 103   def tearDownClass(cls):
 104     pass
 105 
 106   def setUp(self):
 107     self._dump_root = tempfile.mkdtemp()
 108 
 109   def tearDown(self):
 110     ops.reset_default_graph()
 111 
 112     # Tear down temporary dump directory.
 113     if os.path.isdir(self._dump_root):
 114       shutil.rmtree(self._dump_root)
 115 
 116   def _debug_urls(self, run_number=None):
 117     raise NotImplementedError(
 118         "_debug_urls() method is not implemented in the base test class.")
 119 
 120   def _debug_dump_dir(self, run_number=None):
 121     raise NotImplementedError(
 122         "_debug_dump_dir() method is not implemented in the base test class.")
 123 
 124   def _debug_run_and_get_dump(self,
 125                               sess,
 126                               fetches,
 127                               feed_dict=None,
 128                               debug_ops="DebugIdentity",
 129                               tolerate_debug_op_creation_failures=False,
 130                               global_step=-1,
 131                               validate=True,
 132                               expected_partition_graph_count=None):
 133     """Run fetches with debugging and obtain DebugDumpDir.
 134 
 135     Args:
 136       sess: the tf.Session to be used.
 137       fetches: fetches of the Session.run().
 138       feed_dict: feed dict for the Session.run().
 139       debug_ops: name(s) of the debug ops to be used.
 140       tolerate_debug_op_creation_failures: whether to tolerate debug op
 141         creation failures.
 142       global_step: Optional global step.
 143       validate: whether to validate dumped tensors against graph.
 144       expected_partition_graph_count: optional count of partition graphs to
 145         assert on.
 146 
 147     Returns:
 148       1. Return values of the Session.run().
 149       2. The DebugDumpDir object from the debugged run().
 150     """
 151 
 152     run_options = config_pb2.RunOptions(output_partition_graphs=True)
 153     debug_utils.watch_graph(
 154         run_options,
 155         sess.graph,
 156         debug_ops=debug_ops,
 157         debug_urls=self._debug_urls(),
 158         tolerate_debug_op_creation_failures=tolerate_debug_op_creation_failures,
 159         global_step=global_step)
 160     run_metadata = config_pb2.RunMetadata()
 161     run_output = sess.run(fetches,
 162                           feed_dict=feed_dict,
 163                           options=run_options,
 164                           run_metadata=run_metadata)
 165 
 166     if expected_partition_graph_count is not None:
 167       self.assertEqual(expected_partition_graph_count,
 168                        len(run_metadata.partition_graphs))
 169     return run_output, debug_data.DebugDumpDir(
 170         self._dump_root, partition_graphs=run_metadata.partition_graphs,
 171         validate=validate)
 172 
 173   def _generate_dump_from_simple_addition_graph(self):
 174     with session.Session(config=no_rewrite_session_config()) as sess:
 175       u_init_val = np.array([[5.0, 3.0], [-1.0, 0.0]])
 176       v_init_val = np.array([[2.0], [-1.0]])
 177 
 178       # Use node names with overlapping namespace (i.e., parent directory) to
 179       # test concurrent, non-racing directory creation.
 180       u_name = "u"
 181       v_name = "v"
 182       w_name = "w"
 183 
 184       u_init = constant_op.constant(u_init_val, shape=[2, 2])
 185       u = variables.VariableV1(u_init, name=u_name)
 186       v_init = constant_op.constant(v_init_val, shape=[2, 1])
 187       v = variables.VariableV1(v_init, name=v_name)
 188 
 189       w = math_ops.matmul(u, v, name=w_name)
 190 
 191       u.initializer.run()
 192       v.initializer.run()
 193 
 194       run_options = config_pb2.RunOptions(output_partition_graphs=True)
 195       debug_urls = "file://%s" % self._dump_root
 196 
 197       # Add debug tensor watch for u.
 198       debug_utils.add_debug_tensor_watch(
 199           run_options, "%s/read" % u_name, 0, debug_urls=debug_urls)
 200       # Add debug tensor watch for v.
 201       debug_utils.add_debug_tensor_watch(
 202           run_options, "%s/read" % v_name, 0, debug_urls=debug_urls)
 203 
 204       run_metadata = config_pb2.RunMetadata()
 205 
 206       # Invoke Session.run().
 207       sess.run(w, options=run_options, run_metadata=run_metadata)
 208 
 209       self.assertEqual(self._expected_partition_graph_count,
 210                        len(run_metadata.partition_graphs))
 211 
 212       dump = debug_data.DebugDumpDir(
 213           self._dump_root, partition_graphs=run_metadata.partition_graphs)
 214 
 215     simple_add_results = collections.namedtuple("SimpleAddResults", [
 216         "u_init_val", "v_init_val", "u", "v", "w", "u_name", "v_name", "w_name",
 217         "dump"
 218     ])
 219     return simple_add_results(u_init_val, v_init_val, u, v, w, u_name, v_name,
 220                               w_name, dump)
 221 
 222   def testCopyNodesHaveCorrectDebugOpsAndURLsAttributeValues(self):
 223     with session.Session() as sess:
 224       u = variables.VariableV1(2.1, name="u")
 225       v = variables.VariableV1(20.0, name="v")
 226       w = math_ops.multiply(u, v, name="w")
 227 
 228       sess.run(variables.global_variables_initializer())
 229 
 230       run_options = config_pb2.RunOptions(output_partition_graphs=True)
 231       debug_urls = self._debug_urls()
 232       debug_utils.add_debug_tensor_watch(
 233           run_options,
 234           "u",
 235           0, ["DebugNumericSummary(gated_grpc=True)", "DebugIdentity"],
 236           debug_urls=debug_urls)
 237       debug_utils.add_debug_tensor_watch(
 238           run_options, "v", 0, ["DebugNumericSummary"], debug_urls=debug_urls)
 239 
 240       run_metadata = config_pb2.RunMetadata()
 241       r = sess.run(w, options=run_options, run_metadata=run_metadata)
 242       self.assertAllClose(42.0, r)
 243 
 244       u_copy_node_def = None
 245       v_copy_node_def = None
 246       for partition_graph in run_metadata.partition_graphs:
 247         for node_def in partition_graph.node:
 248           if debug_graphs.is_copy_node(node_def.name):
 249             if node_def.name == "__copy_u_0":
 250               u_copy_node_def = node_def
 251             elif node_def.name == "__copy_v_0":
 252               v_copy_node_def = node_def
 253 
 254       self.assertIsNotNone(u_copy_node_def)
 255       debug_ops_spec = u_copy_node_def.attr["debug_ops_spec"].list.s
 256       self.assertEqual(2, len(debug_ops_spec))
 257       self.assertEqual("DebugNumericSummary;%s;1" % debug_urls[0],
 258                        debug_ops_spec[0].decode("utf-8"))
 259       self.assertEqual("DebugIdentity;%s;0" % debug_urls[0],
 260                        debug_ops_spec[1].decode("utf-8"))
 261 
 262       self.assertIsNotNone(v_copy_node_def)
 263       debug_ops_spec = v_copy_node_def.attr["debug_ops_spec"].list.s
 264       self.assertEqual(1, len(debug_ops_spec))
 265       self.assertEqual("DebugNumericSummary;%s;0" % debug_urls[0],
 266                        debug_ops_spec[0].decode("utf-8"))
 267 
 268   def testConcurrentDumpingToPathsWithOverlappingParentDirsWorks(self):
 269     results = self._generate_dump_from_simple_addition_graph()
 270     self.assertTrue(results.dump.loaded_partition_graphs())
 271 
 272     # Since global_step is not explicitly specified, it should take its default
 273     # value: -1.
 274     self.assertEqual(-1, results.dump.core_metadata.global_step)
 275     self.assertGreaterEqual(results.dump.core_metadata.session_run_index, 0)
 276     self.assertGreaterEqual(results.dump.core_metadata.executor_step_index, 0)
 277     self.assertEqual([], results.dump.core_metadata.input_names)
 278     self.assertEqual([results.w.name], results.dump.core_metadata.output_names)
 279     self.assertEqual([], results.dump.core_metadata.target_nodes)
 280 
 281     # Verify the dumped tensor values for u and v.
 282     self.assertEqual(2, results.dump.size)
 283 
 284     self.assertAllClose([results.u_init_val],
 285                         results.dump.get_tensors("%s/read" % results.u_name, 0,
 286                                                  "DebugIdentity"))
 287     self.assertAllClose([results.v_init_val],
 288                         results.dump.get_tensors("%s/read" % results.v_name, 0,
 289                                                  "DebugIdentity"))
 290 
 291     self.assertGreaterEqual(
 292         results.dump.get_rel_timestamps("%s/read" % results.u_name, 0,
 293                                         "DebugIdentity")[0], 0)
 294     self.assertGreaterEqual(
 295         results.dump.get_rel_timestamps("%s/read" % results.v_name, 0,
 296                                         "DebugIdentity")[0], 0)
 297 
 298     self.assertGreater(
 299         results.dump.get_dump_sizes_bytes("%s/read" % results.u_name, 0,
 300                                           "DebugIdentity")[0], 0)
 301     self.assertGreater(
 302         results.dump.get_dump_sizes_bytes("%s/read" % results.v_name, 0,
 303                                           "DebugIdentity")[0], 0)
 304 
 305   def testGetOpTypeWorks(self):
 306     results = self._generate_dump_from_simple_addition_graph()
 307 
 308     self.assertEqual(results.u.op.type,
 309                      results.dump.node_op_type(results.u_name))
 310     self.assertIn(results.v.op.type, results.dump.node_op_type(results.v_name))
 311     self.assertIn(results.w.op.type, results.dump.node_op_type(results.w_name))
 312 
 313     with self.assertRaisesRegexp(
 314         ValueError, r"None of the .* device\(s\) has a node named "):
 315       results.dump.node_op_type("foo_bar")

 317   def testDumpStringTensorsWorks(self):
 318     with session.Session(config=no_rewrite_session_config()) as sess:
 319       str1_init_val = np.array(b"abc")
 320       str2_init_val = np.array(b"def")
 321 
 322       str1_init = constant_op.constant(str1_init_val)
 323       str2_init = constant_op.constant(str2_init_val)
 324 
 325       str1_name = "str1"
 326       str2_name = "str2"
 327       str1 = variables.VariableV1(str1_init, name=str1_name)
 328       str2 = variables.VariableV1(str2_init, name=str2_name)
 329       # Concatenate str1 and str2
 330       str_concat = math_ops.add(str1, str2, name="str_concat")
 331 
 332       str1.initializer.run()
 333       str2.initializer.run()
 334 
 335       run_options = config_pb2.RunOptions(output_partition_graphs=True)
 336       debug_urls = self._debug_urls()
 337 
 338       # Add debug tensor watch for u.
 339       debug_utils.add_debug_tensor_watch(
 340           run_options, "%s/read" % str1_name, 0, debug_urls=debug_urls)
 341       # Add debug tensor watch for v.
 342       debug_utils.add_debug_tensor_watch(
 343           run_options, "%s/read" % str2_name, 0, debug_urls=debug_urls)
 344 
 345       run_metadata = config_pb2.RunMetadata()
 346       sess.run(str_concat, options=run_options, run_metadata=run_metadata)
 347 
 348       # String ops are located on CPU.
 349       self.assertEqual(1, len(run_metadata.partition_graphs))
 350 
 351       dump = debug_data.DebugDumpDir(
 352           self._dump_root, partition_graphs=run_metadata.partition_graphs)
 353 
 354       self.assertIn(str1_name, dump.nodes())
 355       self.assertIn(str2_name, dump.nodes())
 356 
 357       self.assertEqual(2, dump.size)
 358 
 359       self.assertEqual([str1_init_val],
 360                        dump.get_tensors("%s/read" % str1_name, 0,
 361                                         "DebugIdentity"))
 362       self.assertEqual([str2_init_val],
 363                        dump.get_tensors("%s/read" % str2_name, 0,
 364                                         "DebugIdentity"))
 365 
 366       self.assertGreaterEqual(
 367           dump.get_rel_timestamps("%s/read" % str1_name, 0, "DebugIdentity")[0],
 368           0)
 369       self.assertGreaterEqual(
 370           dump.get_rel_timestamps("%s/read" % str2_name, 0, "DebugIdentity")[0],
 371           0)
 372 
 373       self.assertGreater(
 374           dump.get_dump_sizes_bytes("%s/read" % str1_name, 0,
 375                                     "DebugIdentity")[0], 0)
 376       self.assertGreater(
 377           dump.get_dump_sizes_bytes("%s/read" % str2_name, 0,
 378                                     "DebugIdentity")[0], 0)
 379 
 380   def testDumpUninitializedVariable(self):
 381     op_namespace = "testDumpUninitializedVariable"
 382     with session.Session() as sess:
 383       u_init_val = np.array([[5.0, 3.0], [-1.0, 0.0]])
 384       s_init_val = b"str1"
 385 
 386       u_name = "%s/u" % op_namespace
 387       s_name = "%s/s" % op_namespace
 388 
 389       u_init = constant_op.constant(u_init_val, shape=[2, 2])
 390       u = variables.VariableV1(u_init, name=u_name)
 391       s_init = constant_op.constant(s_init_val)
 392       s = variables.VariableV1(s_init, name=s_name)
 393 
 394       run_options = config_pb2.RunOptions(output_partition_graphs=True)
 395       debug_urls = self._debug_urls()
 396 
 397       # Add debug tensor watch for u.
 398       debug_utils.add_debug_tensor_watch(
 399           run_options, u_name, 0, debug_urls=debug_urls)
 400       debug_utils.add_debug_tensor_watch(
 401           run_options, s_name, 0, debug_urls=debug_urls)
 402 
 403       run_metadata = config_pb2.RunMetadata()
 404 
 405       # Initialize u and s.
 406       sess.run(variables.global_variables_initializer(),
 407                options=run_options,
 408                run_metadata=run_metadata)
 409 
 410       # Verify the dump file for the uninitialized value of u.
 411       dump = debug_data.DebugDumpDir(
 412           self._dump_root, partition_graphs=run_metadata.partition_graphs)
 413 
 414       self.assertEqual(2, dump.size)
 415       self.assertEqual(self._expected_partition_graph_count,
 416                        len(run_metadata.partition_graphs))
 417 
 418       # Verify that the variable is properly initialized by the run() call.
 419       u_vals = dump.get_tensors(u_name, 0, "DebugIdentity")
 420       s_vals = dump.get_tensors(s_name, 0, "DebugIdentity")
 421       self.assertEqual(1, len(u_vals))
 422       self.assertIsInstance(u_vals[0], debug_data.InconvertibleTensorProto)
 423       self.assertFalse(u_vals[0].initialized)
 424       self.assertEqual(1, len(s_vals))
 425       self.assertIsInstance(s_vals[0], debug_data.InconvertibleTensorProto)
 426       self.assertFalse(s_vals[0].initialized)
 427 
 428       # Call run() again, to check that u is initialized properly.
 429       self.assertAllClose(u_init_val, sess.run(u))
 430       self.assertEqual(s_init_val, sess.run(s))
 431 
 432   def testDebugWhileLoopGeneratesMultipleDumps(self):
 433     with session.Session(config=no_rewrite_session_config()) as sess:
 434       num_iter = 10
 435 
 436       # "u" is the Variable being updated in the loop.
 437       u_name = "testDumpToFileWhileLoop/u"
 438       u_namespace = u_name.split("/")[0]
 439 
 440       u_init_val = np.array(11.0)
 441       u_init = constant_op.constant(u_init_val)
 442       u = variables.VariableV1(u_init, name=u_name)
 443 
 444       # "v" is the increment.
 445       v_name = "testDumpToFileWhileLoop/v"
 446       v_namespace = v_name.split("/")[0]
 447 
 448       v_init_val = np.array(2.0)
 449       v_init = constant_op.constant(v_init_val)
 450       v = variables.VariableV1(v_init, name=v_name)
 451 
 452       u.initializer.run()
 453       v.initializer.run()
 454 
 455       i = constant_op.constant(0, name="testDumpToFileWhileLoop/i")
 456 
 457       def cond(i):
 458         return math_ops.less(i, num_iter)
 459 
 460       def body(i):
 461         new_u = state_ops.assign_add(u, v)
 462         new_i = math_ops.add(i, 1)
 463         op = control_flow_ops.group(new_u)
 464         new_i = control_flow_ops.with_dependencies([op], new_i)
 465         return [new_i]
 466 
 467       loop = control_flow_ops.while_loop(
 468           cond, body, [i], parallel_iterations=10)
 469 
 470       # Create RunOptions for debug-watching tensors
 471       run_options = config_pb2.RunOptions(output_partition_graphs=True)
 472       debug_urls = self._debug_urls()
 473 
 474       # Add debug tensor watch for u.
 475       debug_utils.add_debug_tensor_watch(
 476           run_options, u_name, 0, debug_urls=debug_urls)
 477       # Add debug tensor watch for v.
 478       debug_utils.add_debug_tensor_watch(
 479           run_options, "%s/read" % v_name, 0, debug_urls=debug_urls)
 480       # Add debug tensor watch for while/Identity.
 481       debug_utils.add_debug_tensor_watch(
 482           run_options, "while/Identity", 0, debug_urls=debug_urls)
 483       # Add debug tensor watch for while/Add/y.
 484       debug_utils.add_debug_tensor_watch(
 485           run_options, "while/Add/y", 0, debug_urls=debug_urls)
 486 
 487       run_metadata = config_pb2.RunMetadata()
 488       r = sess.run(loop, options=run_options, run_metadata=run_metadata)
 489 
 490       self.assertEqual(self._expected_partition_graph_count,
 491                        len(run_metadata.partition_graphs))
 492 
 493       self.assertEqual(num_iter, r)
 494       u_val_final = sess.run(u)
 495       self.assertAllClose(u_init_val + num_iter * v_init_val, u_val_final)
 496 
 497       # Verify dump files
 498       self.assertTrue(os.path.isdir(self._dump_root))
 499 
 500       u_glob_out = glob.glob(os.path.join(self._dump_root, "*", u_namespace))
 501       v_glob_out = glob.glob(os.path.join(
 502           self._dump_root, "*", v_namespace, "v"))
 503       self.assertTrue(os.path.isdir(u_glob_out[0]))
 504       self.assertTrue(os.path.isdir(v_glob_out[0]))
 505 
 506       dump = debug_data.DebugDumpDir(
 507           self._dump_root, partition_graphs=run_metadata.partition_graphs)
 508 
 509       # Expected dumped tensors: u, v/read, 10 iterations of while/Identity,
 510       # and 10 iterations of while/Add/y.
 511       self.assertEqual(1 + 1 + num_iter + num_iter, dump.size)
 512 
 513       # Verify tensor values.
 514       self.assertAllClose([u_init_val],
 515                           dump.get_tensors(u_name, 0, "DebugIdentity"))
 516       self.assertAllClose([v_init_val],
 517                           dump.get_tensors("%s/read" % v_name, 0,
 518                                            "DebugIdentity"))
 519 
 520       while_id_tensors = dump.get_tensors("while/Identity", 0, "DebugIdentity")
 521       self.assertEqual(10, len(while_id_tensors))
 522       for k in xrange(len(while_id_tensors)):
 523         self.assertAllClose(np.array(k), while_id_tensors[k])
 524 
 525       # Verify ascending timestamps from the while loops.
 526       while_id_rel_timestamps = dump.get_rel_timestamps("while/Identity", 0,
 527                                                         "DebugIdentity")
 528       while_id_dump_sizes_bytes = dump.get_dump_sizes_bytes("while/Identity", 0,
 529                                                             "DebugIdentity")
 530       self.assertEqual(10, len(while_id_rel_timestamps))
 531       prev_rel_time = 0
 532       prev_dump_size_bytes = while_id_dump_sizes_bytes[0]
 533       for rel_time, dump_size_bytes in zip(while_id_rel_timestamps,
 534                                            while_id_dump_sizes_bytes):
 535         self.assertGreaterEqual(rel_time, prev_rel_time)
 536         self.assertEqual(dump_size_bytes, prev_dump_size_bytes)
 537         prev_rel_time = rel_time
 538         prev_dump_size_bytes = dump_size_bytes
 539 
 540       # Test querying debug watch keys from node name.
 541       watch_keys = dump.debug_watch_keys("while/Identity")
 542       self.assertEqual(["while/Identity:0:DebugIdentity"], watch_keys)
 543 
 544       # Test querying debug datum instances from debug watch key.
 545       self.assertEqual(10, len(dump.watch_key_to_data(watch_keys[0])))
 546       self.assertEqual([], dump.watch_key_to_data("foo"))

 548   def testDebugWhileLoopWatchingWholeGraphWorks(self):
 549     with session.Session() as sess:
 550       loop_body = lambda i: math_ops.add(i, 2)
 551       loop_cond = lambda i: math_ops.less(i, 16)

 565   def testDebugTrainingDynamicRNNWorks(self):
 566     with session.Session() as sess:
 567       input_size = 3
 568       state_size = 2
 569       time_steps = 4
 570       batch_size = 2
 571 
 572       input_values = np.random.randn(time_steps, batch_size, input_size)
 573       sequence_length = np.random.randint(0, time_steps, size=batch_size)
 574       concat_inputs = array_ops.placeholder(
 575           dtypes.float32, shape=(time_steps, batch_size, input_size))
 576 
 577       outputs_dynamic, _ = rnn.dynamic_rnn(
 578           _RNNCellForTest(input_size, state_size),
 579           inputs=concat_inputs,
 580           sequence_length=sequence_length,
 581           time_major=True,
 582           dtype=dtypes.float32)
 583       toy_loss = math_ops.reduce_sum(outputs_dynamic * outputs_dynamic)
 584       train_op = gradient_descent.GradientDescentOptimizer(
 585           learning_rate=0.1).minimize(toy_loss, name="train_op")
 586 
 587       sess.run(variables.global_variables_initializer())
 588 
 589       run_options = config_pb2.RunOptions(output_partition_graphs=True)
 590       debug_utils.watch_graph_with_blacklists(
 591           run_options,
 592           sess.graph,
 593           node_name_regex_blacklist="(.*rnn/while/.*|.*TensorArray.*)",
 594           debug_urls=self._debug_urls())
 595       # b/36870549: Nodes with these name patterns need to be excluded from
 596       # tfdbg in order to prevent MSAN warnings of uninitialized Tensors
 597       # under both file:// and grpc:// debug URL schemes.
 598 
 599       run_metadata = config_pb2.RunMetadata()
 600       sess.run(train_op, feed_dict={concat_inputs: input_values},
 601                options=run_options, run_metadata=run_metadata)
 602 
 603       debug_data.DebugDumpDir(
 604           self._dump_root, partition_graphs=run_metadata.partition_graphs)

 621   def testFindNodesWithBadTensorValues(self):
 622     with session.Session() as sess:
 623       u_name = "testFindNodesWithBadTensorValues/u"
 624       v_name = "testFindNodesWithBadTensorValues/v"
 625       w_name = "testFindNodesWithBadTensorValues/w"
 626       x_name = "testFindNodesWithBadTensorValues/x"
 627       y_name = "testFindNodesWithBadTensorValues/y"
 628       z_name = "testFindNodesWithBadTensorValues/z"
 629 
 630       u_init = constant_op.constant([2.0, 4.0])
 631       u = variables.VariableV1(u_init, name=u_name)
 632       v_init = constant_op.constant([2.0, 1.0])
 633       v = variables.VariableV1(v_init, name=v_name)
 634 
 635       # Expected output: [0.0, 3.0]
 636       w = math_ops.subtract(u, v, name=w_name)
 637 
 638       # Expected output: [inf, 1.3333]
 639       x = math_ops.div(u, w, name=x_name)
 640 
 641       # Expected output: [nan, 4.0]
 642       y = math_ops.multiply(w, x, name=y_name)
 643 
 644       z = math_ops.multiply(y, y, name=z_name)
 645 
 646       u.initializer.run()
 647       v.initializer.run()
 648 
 649       _, dump = self._debug_run_and_get_dump(
 650           sess, z,
 651           expected_partition_graph_count=self._expected_partition_graph_count)
 652 
 653       def has_bad_value(_, tensor):
 654         return np.any(np.isnan(tensor)) or np.any(np.isinf(tensor))
 655 
 656       # Find all "offending tensors".
 657       bad_data = dump.find(has_bad_value)
 658 
 659       # Verify that the nodes with bad values are caught through running find
 660       # on the debug dump.
 661       self.assertEqual(3, len(bad_data))
 662       self.assertEqual(x_name, bad_data[0].node_name)
 663       self.assertEqual(y_name, bad_data[1].node_name)
 664       self.assertEqual(z_name, bad_data[2].node_name)
 665 
 666       # Test first_n kwarg of find(): Find the first offending tensor.
 667       first_bad_datum = dump.find(has_bad_value, first_n=1)
 668 
 669       self.assertEqual(1, len(first_bad_datum))
 670       self.assertEqual(x_name, first_bad_datum[0].node_name)
 671

 890   def testCausalityCheckOnDumpsDetectsWrongTemporalOrder(self):
 891     with session.Session(config=no_rewrite_session_config()) as sess:
 892       u_name = "testDumpCausalityCheck/u"
 893       v_name = "testDumpCausalityCheck/v"
 894       w_name = "testDumpCausalityCheck/w"
 895 
 896       u_init = constant_op.constant([2.0, 4.0])
 897       u = variables.VariableV1(u_init, name=u_name)
 898       v = math_ops.add(u, u, name=v_name)
 899       w = math_ops.add(v, v, name=w_name)
 900 
 901       u.initializer.run()
 902 
 903       run_options = config_pb2.RunOptions(output_partition_graphs=True)
 904       debug_utils.watch_graph(
 905           run_options,
 906           sess.graph,
 907           debug_ops=["DebugIdentity"],
 908           debug_urls=self._debug_urls())
 909 
 910       run_metadata = config_pb2.RunMetadata()
 911       sess.run(w, options=run_options, run_metadata=run_metadata)
 912 
 913       self.assertEqual(self._expected_partition_graph_count,
 914                        len(run_metadata.partition_graphs))
 915 
 916       # First, loading the original dump without supplying the
 917       # partition_graphs should not cause a LookupError, validation occurs
 918       # only with partition_graphs loaded.
 919       debug_data.DebugDumpDir(self._dump_root)
 920 
 921       # Now, loading the original dump with partition graphs supplied should
 922       # succeed. The validation should pass quietly.
 923       dump = debug_data.DebugDumpDir(
 924           self._dump_root, partition_graphs=run_metadata.partition_graphs)
 925 
 926       # Get the dump file names and compute their timestamps.
 927       self.assertEqual(
 928           1, len(dump.get_tensor_file_paths(v_name, 0, "DebugIdentity")))
 929       v_file_path = dump.get_tensor_file_paths(v_name, 0, "DebugIdentity")[0]
 930 
 931       self.assertEqual(
 932           1, len(dump.get_tensor_file_paths(w_name, 0, "DebugIdentity")))
 933       w_file_path = dump.get_tensor_file_paths(w_name, 0, "DebugIdentity")[0]
 934 
 935       v_timestamp = int(v_file_path[v_file_path.rindex("_") + 1:])
 936       w_timestamp = int(w_file_path[w_file_path.rindex("_") + 1:])
 937 
 938       # Swap and slightly shift the time stamps of the last two dumped tensors,
 939       # to simulate "causality violation", which can happen if the dump
 940       # directory contains incomplete data and/or mixes data from different
 941       # Session.run() calls.
 942       v_file_path_1 = v_file_path[:v_file_path.rindex(
 943           "_")] + "_%d" % w_timestamp
 944       w_file_path_1 = w_file_path[:w_file_path.rindex("_")] + "_%d" % (
 945           v_timestamp - 1)
 946 
 947       os.rename(v_file_path, v_file_path_1)
 948       os.rename(w_file_path, w_file_path_1)
 949 
 950       # Load the dump directory again. Now a ValueError is expected to be
 951       # raised due to the timestamp swap.
 952       with self.assertRaisesRegexp(ValueError, "Causality violated"):
 953         dump = debug_data.DebugDumpDir(
 954             self._dump_root, partition_graphs=run_metadata.partition_graphs)
 955 
 956       # Loading the dump directory with kwarg "validate" set explicitly to
 957       # False should get rid of the error.
 958       dump = debug_data.DebugDumpDir(
 959           self._dump_root,
 960           partition_graphs=run_metadata.partition_graphs,
 961           validate=False)
 962 
 963       # Next, set the two times stamps to be the same, which should be fine.
 964       v_file_path_2 = v_file_path[:v_file_path.rindex(
 965           "_")] + "_%d" % w_timestamp
 966       w_file_path_2 = w_file_path[:w_file_path.rindex(
 967           "_")] + "_%d" % w_timestamp
 968 
 969       os.rename(v_file_path_1, v_file_path_2)
 970       os.rename(w_file_path_1, w_file_path_2)
 971 
 972       debug_data.DebugDumpDir(
 973           self._dump_root, partition_graphs=run_metadata.partition_graphs)
 974 
 975   def testWatchingOnlyOneOfTwoOutputSlotsDoesNotLeadToCausalityFailure(self):
 976     with session.Session() as sess:
 977       x_name = "oneOfTwoSlots/x"
 978       u_name = "oneOfTwoSlots/u"
 979       v_name = "oneOfTwoSlots/v"
 980       w_name = "oneOfTwoSlots/w"
 981       y_name = "oneOfTwoSlots/y"
 982 
 983       x = variables.VariableV1([1, 3, 3, 7], dtype=dtypes.int32, name=x_name)
 984       sess.run(x.initializer)
 985 
 986       unique_x, indices, _ = array_ops.unique_with_counts(x, name=u_name)
 987 
 988       v = math_ops.add(unique_x, unique_x, name=v_name)
 989       w = math_ops.add(indices, indices, name=w_name)
 990       y = math_ops.add(w, w, name=y_name)
 991 
 992       run_options = config_pb2.RunOptions(output_partition_graphs=True)
 993       # Watch only the first output slot of u, even though it has two output
 994       # slots.
 995       debug_utils.add_debug_tensor_watch(
 996           run_options, u_name, 0, debug_urls=self._debug_urls())
 997       debug_utils.add_debug_tensor_watch(
 998           run_options, w_name, 0, debug_urls=self._debug_urls())
 999       debug_utils.add_debug_tensor_watch(
1000           run_options, y_name, 0, debug_urls=self._debug_urls())
1001 
1002       run_metadata = config_pb2.RunMetadata()
1003       sess.run([v, y], options=run_options, run_metadata=run_metadata)
1004 
1005       dump = debug_data.DebugDumpDir(
1006           self._dump_root,
1007           partition_graphs=run_metadata.partition_graphs,
1008           validate=True)
1009 
1010       self.assertAllClose([1, 3, 7],
1011                           dump.get_tensors(u_name, 0, "DebugIdentity")[0])

1013   def testOutputSlotWithoutOutgoingEdgeCanBeWatched(self):
1014     """Test watching output slots not attached to any outgoing edges."""
1015 
1016     with session.Session(config=no_rewrite_session_config()) as sess:
1017       u_init_val = np.array([[5.0, 3.0], [-1.0, 0.0]])
1018       u = constant_op.constant(u_init_val, shape=[2, 2], name="u")
1019 
1020       # Create a control edge from a node with an output: From u to z.
1021       # Node u will get executed only because of the control edge. The output
1022       # tensor u:0 is not attached to any outgoing edge in the graph. This test
1023       # checks that the debugger can watch such a tensor.
1024       with ops.control_dependencies([u]):
1025         z = control_flow_ops.no_op(name="z")
1026 
1027       _, dump = self._debug_run_and_get_dump(sess, z)
1028 
1029       # Assert that the DebugIdentity watch on u works properly.
1030       self.assertEqual(1, len(dump.dumped_tensor_data))
1031       datum = dump.dumped_tensor_data[0]
1032       self.assertEqual("u", datum.node_name)
1033       self.assertEqual(0, datum.output_slot)
1034       self.assertEqual("DebugIdentity", datum.debug_op)
1035       self.assertAllClose([[5.0, 3.0], [-1.0, 0.0]], datum.get_tensor())

1037   def testWatchingVariableUpdateOpsSeesUpdatedValues(self):
1038     """Watch output slots on Variable-updating ops, with no emitted edges."""
1039 
1040     with session.Session(config=no_rewrite_session_config()) as sess:
1041       u_init = constant_op.constant(10.0)
1042       u = variables.VariableV1(u_init, name="gdo/u")
1043       v_init = constant_op.constant(20.0)
1044       v = variables.VariableV1(v_init, name="gdo/v")
1045 
1046       w = math_ops.multiply(u, v, name="gdo/w")
1047       # gdo stands for GradientDescentOptimizer.
1048 
1049       train_op = gradient_descent.GradientDescentOptimizer(
1050           learning_rate=0.1).minimize(
1051               w, name="gdo/train")
1052 
1053       u.initializer.run()
1054       v.initializer.run()
1055 
1056       _, dump = self._debug_run_and_get_dump(sess, train_op)
1057 
1058       update_u_data = dump.watch_key_to_data(
1059           "gdo/train/update_gdo/u/ApplyGradientDescent:0:DebugIdentity")
1060       self.assertEqual(1, len(update_u_data))
1061 
1062       # Gradient descent on u: w = u * v, so dw / du = v.
1063       # Updated value of u should be:
1064       #   10.0 - learning_rate * v = 10.0 - 0.1 * 20.0 = 8.0
1065       self.assertAllClose(8.0, update_u_data[0].get_tensor())
1066 
1067       update_v_data = dump.watch_key_to_data(
1068           "gdo/train/update_gdo/v/ApplyGradientDescent:0:DebugIdentity")
1069       self.assertEqual(1, len(update_v_data))
1070 
1071       # Gradient descent on u: w = u * v, so dw / dv = u.
1072       # Updated value of u should be:
1073       #   20.0 - learning_rate * u = 20.0 - 0.1 * 10.0 = 19.0
1074       self.assertAllClose(19.0, update_v_data[0].get_tensor())
1075 
1076       # Verify that the Variables u and v are updated properly.
1077       self.assertAllClose(8.0, sess.run(u))
1078       self.assertAllClose(19.0, sess.run(v))

1080   def testAllowsWatchingUnconnectedOutputTensor(self):
1081     """Watch an output slot not emitting any edges.
1082 
1083     (Not even control edges from the node.)
1084     """
1085 
1086     with session.Session() as sess:
1087       x_init = constant_op.constant([2, 2, 3, 5, 5])
1088       x = variables.VariableV1(x_init, name="unconnected/x")
1089 
1090       # The UniqueOp (tf.unique) has two output slots. Use only slot 0 in the
1091       # graph. Let the debugger watch the unused slot 1.
1092       unique_x, _ = array_ops.unique(x, name="unconnected/unique_x")
1093       y = math_ops.add(unique_x, [0, 1, 2], name="unconnected/y")
1094 
1095       x.initializer.run()
1096 
1097       # Verify that only slot 0 of unique_x has recipients, while slot 1 of the
1098       # same node does not have recipients.
1099       unique_x_slot_0_recipients = []
1100       unique_x_slot_1_recipients = []
1101       for op in sess.graph.get_operations():
1102         for inp in op.inputs:
1103           if inp.name == "unconnected/unique_x:0":
1104             unique_x_slot_0_recipients.append(op.name)
1105           elif inp.name == "unconnected/unique_x:1":
1106             unique_x_slot_1_recipients.append(op.name)
1107 
1108       self.assertEqual(["unconnected/y"], unique_x_slot_0_recipients)
1109       self.assertEqual([], unique_x_slot_1_recipients)
1110 
1111       y_result, dump = self._debug_run_and_get_dump(sess, y)
1112       self.assertAllClose([2, 4, 7], y_result)
1113 
1114       # Assert that the connected slot (slot 0) is dumped properly.
1115       unique_x_slot_0_dumps = dump.watch_key_to_data(
1116           "unconnected/unique_x:0:DebugIdentity")
1117       self.assertEqual(1, len(unique_x_slot_0_dumps))
1118       self.assertEqual("unconnected/unique_x",
1119                        unique_x_slot_0_dumps[0].node_name)
1120       self.assertEqual(0, unique_x_slot_0_dumps[0].output_slot)
1121       self.assertAllClose([2, 3, 5], unique_x_slot_0_dumps[0].get_tensor())
1122 
1123       # Assert that the unconnected slot (slot 1) is dumped properly.
1124       unique_x_slot_1_dumps = dump.watch_key_to_data(
1125           "unconnected/unique_x:1:DebugIdentity")
1126       self.assertEqual(1, len(unique_x_slot_1_dumps))
1127       self.assertEqual("unconnected/unique_x",
1128                        unique_x_slot_1_dumps[0].node_name)
1129       self.assertEqual(1, unique_x_slot_1_dumps[0].output_slot)
1130       self.assertAllClose([0, 0, 1, 2, 2],
1131                           unique_x_slot_1_dumps[0].get_tensor())

1133   def testSuccessiveDebuggingRunsIncreasesCounters(self):
1134     """Test repeated Session.run() calls with debugger increments counters."""
1135 
1136     with session.Session() as sess:
1137       ph = array_ops.placeholder(dtypes.float32, name="successive/ph")
1138       x = array_ops.transpose(ph, name="mismatch/x")
1139       y = array_ops.squeeze(ph, name="mismatch/y")
1140 
1141       _, dump1 = self._debug_run_and_get_dump(
1142           sess, x, feed_dict={ph: np.array([[7.0, 8.0]])}, global_step=1)
1143       self.assertEqual(1, dump1.core_metadata.global_step)
1144       self.assertGreaterEqual(dump1.core_metadata.session_run_index, 0)
1145       self.assertEqual(0, dump1.core_metadata.executor_step_index)
1146       self.assertEqual([ph.name], dump1.core_metadata.input_names)
1147       self.assertEqual([x.name], dump1.core_metadata.output_names)
1148       self.assertEqual([], dump1.core_metadata.target_nodes)
1149       shutil.rmtree(self._dump_root)
1150 
1151       # Calling run() with the same feed, same output and same debug watch
1152       # options should increment both session_run_index and
1153       # executor_step_index.
1154       _, dump2 = self._debug_run_and_get_dump(
1155           sess, x, feed_dict={ph: np.array([[7.0, 8.0]])}, global_step=2)
1156       self.assertEqual(2, dump2.core_metadata.global_step)
1157       self.assertEqual(dump1.core_metadata.session_run_index + 1,
1158                        dump2.core_metadata.session_run_index)
1159       self.assertEqual(dump1.core_metadata.executor_step_index + 1,
1160                        dump2.core_metadata.executor_step_index)
1161       self.assertEqual([ph.name], dump2.core_metadata.input_names)
1162       self.assertEqual([x.name], dump2.core_metadata.output_names)
1163       self.assertEqual([], dump2.core_metadata.target_nodes)
1164       shutil.rmtree(self._dump_root)
1165 
1166       run_options = config_pb2.RunOptions(output_partition_graphs=True)
1167       debug_utils.watch_graph(
1168           run_options, sess.graph, debug_urls=self._debug_urls(), global_step=3)
1169 
1170       # Calling run() with a different output should increment
1171       # session_run_index, but not executor_step_index.
1172       _, dump3 = self._debug_run_and_get_dump(
1173           sess, y, feed_dict={ph: np.array([[7.0, 8.0]])}, global_step=3)
1174       self.assertEqual(3, dump3.core_metadata.global_step)
1175       self.assertEqual(dump2.core_metadata.session_run_index + 1,
1176                        dump3.core_metadata.session_run_index)
1177       self.assertEqual(0, dump3.core_metadata.executor_step_index)
1178       self.assertEqual([ph.name], dump3.core_metadata.input_names)
1179       self.assertEqual([y.name], dump3.core_metadata.output_names)
1180       self.assertEqual([], dump3.core_metadata.target_nodes)

1182   def testDebuggingDuringOpError(self):
1183     """Test the debug tensor dumping when error occurs in graph runtime."""
1184 
1185     with session.Session() as sess:
1186       ph = array_ops.placeholder(dtypes.float32, name="mismatch/ph")
1187       x = array_ops.transpose(ph, name="mismatch/x")
1188       m = constant_op.constant(
1189           np.array(
1190               [[1.0, 2.0]], dtype=np.float32), name="mismatch/m")
1191       y = math_ops.matmul(m, x, name="mismatch/y")
1192 
1193       run_options = config_pb2.RunOptions(output_partition_graphs=True)
1194       debug_utils.watch_graph(
1195           run_options,
1196           sess.graph,
1197           debug_ops=["DebugIdentity"],
1198           debug_urls=self._debug_urls())
1199 
1200       with self.assertRaises(errors.OpError):
1201         sess.run(y,
1202                  options=run_options,
1203                  feed_dict={ph: np.array([[-3.0], [0.0]])})
1204 
1205       dump = debug_data.DebugDumpDir(self._dump_root)
1206 
1207       self.assertGreaterEqual(dump.core_metadata.session_run_index, 0)
1208       self.assertGreaterEqual(dump.core_metadata.executor_step_index, 0)
1209       self.assertEqual([ph.name], dump.core_metadata.input_names)
1210       self.assertEqual([y.name], dump.core_metadata.output_names)
1211       self.assertEqual([], dump.core_metadata.target_nodes)
1212 
1213       # Despite the fact that the run() call errored out and partition_graphs
1214       # are not available via run_metadata, the partition graphs should still
1215       # have been loaded from the dump directory.
1216       self.assertTrue(dump.loaded_partition_graphs())
1217 
1218       m_dumps = dump.watch_key_to_data("mismatch/m:0:DebugIdentity")
1219       self.assertEqual(1, len(m_dumps))
1220       self.assertAllClose(np.array([[1.0, 2.0]]), m_dumps[0].get_tensor())
1221 
1222       x_dumps = dump.watch_key_to_data("mismatch/x:0:DebugIdentity")
1223       self.assertEqual(1, len(x_dumps))
1224       self.assertAllClose(np.array([[-3.0, 0.0]]), x_dumps[0].get_tensor())

1436   def testLookUpNodePythonTracebackWorks(self):
1437     with session.Session() as sess:
1438       u_init = constant_op.constant(10.0)
1439       u = variables.VariableV1(u_init, name="traceback/u")
1440       v_init = constant_op.constant(20.0)
1441       v = variables.VariableV1(v_init, name="traceback/v")
1442 
1443       w = math_ops.multiply(u, v, name="traceback/w")
1444 
1445       sess.run(variables.global_variables_initializer())
1446       _, dump = self._debug_run_and_get_dump(sess, w)
1447 
1448       # Prior to setting the Python graph, attempts to do traceback lookup
1449       # should lead to exceptions.
1450       with self.assertRaisesRegexp(
1451           LookupError, "Python graph is not available for traceback lookup"):
1452         dump.node_traceback("traceback/w")
1453 
1454       dump.set_python_graph(sess.graph)
1455 
1456       # After setting the Python graph, attempts to look up nonexistent nodes
1457       # should lead to exceptions.
1458       with self.assertRaisesRegexp(KeyError,
1459                                    r"Cannot find node \"foo\" in Python graph"):
1460         dump.node_traceback("foo")
1461 
1462       # Lookup should work with node name input.
1463       traceback = dump.node_traceback("traceback/w")
1464       self.assertIsInstance(traceback, list)
1465       self.assertGreater(len(traceback), 0)
1466       for trace in traceback:
1467         self.assertIsInstance(trace, tuple)
1468 
1469       # Lookup should also work with tensor name input.
1470       traceback = dump.node_traceback("traceback/w:0")
1471       self.assertIsInstance(traceback, list)
1472       self.assertGreater(len(traceback), 0)
1473       for trace in traceback:
1474         self.assertIsInstance(trace, tuple)
1475 
1476 
1477 class DebugConcurrentRunCallsTest(test_util.TensorFlowTestCase):
1478   """Test for debugging concurrent Session.run() calls."""
1479 
1480   def _get_concurrent_debug_urls(self):
1481     """Abstract method to generate debug URLs for concurrent debugged runs."""
1482     raise NotImplementedError(
1483         "_get_concurrent_debug_urls is not implemented in the base test class")
1484 
1485   def testDebugConcurrentVariableUpdates(self):
1486     if test.is_gpu_available():
1487       self.skipTest("No testing concurrent runs on a single GPU.")
1488 
1489     with session.Session() as sess:
1490       v = variables.VariableV1(30.0, name="v")
1491       constants = []
1492       for i in xrange(self._num_concurrent_runs):
1493         constants.append(constant_op.constant(1.0, name="c%d" % i))
1494       incs = [
1495           state_ops.assign_add(
1496               v, c, use_locking=True, name=("inc%d" % i))
1497           for (i, c) in enumerate(constants)
1498       ]
1499       sess.run(v.initializer)
1500 
1501       concurrent_debug_urls = self._get_concurrent_debug_urls()
1502 
1503       def inc_job(index):
1504         run_options = config_pb2.RunOptions(output_partition_graphs=True)
1505         debug_utils.watch_graph(
1506             run_options, sess.graph, debug_urls=concurrent_debug_urls[index])
1507         for _ in xrange(100):
1508           sess.run(incs[index], options=run_options)
1509 
1510       inc_threads = []
1511       for index in xrange(self._num_concurrent_runs):
1512         inc_thread = threading.Thread(target=functools.partial(inc_job, index))
1513         inc_thread.start()
1514         inc_threads.append(inc_thread)
1515       for inc_thread in inc_threads:
1516         inc_thread.join()
1517 
1518       self.assertAllClose(30.0 + 1.0 * self._num_concurrent_runs * 100,
1519                           sess.run(v))
1520 
1521       all_session_run_indices = []
1522       for index in xrange(self._num_concurrent_runs):
1523         dump = debug_data.DebugDumpDir(self._dump_roots[index])
1524         self.assertTrue(dump.loaded_partition_graphs())
1525 
1526         v_data = dump.get_tensors("v", 0, "DebugIdentity")
1527         self.assertEqual(100, len(v_data))
1528 
1529         # Examine all the core metadata files
1530         core_metadata_files = glob.glob(
1531             os.path.join(self._dump_roots[index], "_tfdbg_core*"))
1532 
1533         timestamps = []
1534         session_run_indices = []
1535         executor_step_indices = []
1536         for core_metadata_file in core_metadata_files:
1537           with open(core_metadata_file, "rb") as f:
1538             event = event_pb2.Event()
1539             event.ParseFromString(f.read())
1540             core_metadata = (
1541                 debug_data.extract_core_metadata_from_event_proto(event))
1542             timestamps.append(event.wall_time)
1543             session_run_indices.append(core_metadata.session_run_index)
1544             executor_step_indices.append(core_metadata.executor_step_index)
1545 
1546         all_session_run_indices.extend(session_run_indices)
1547 
1548         # Assert that executor_step_index increases by one at a time.
1549         executor_step_indices = zip(timestamps, executor_step_indices)
1550         executor_step_indices = sorted(
1551             executor_step_indices, key=lambda x: x[0])
1552         for i in xrange(len(executor_step_indices) - 1):
1553           self.assertEquals(executor_step_indices[i][1] + 1,
1554                             executor_step_indices[i + 1][1])
1555 
1556         # Assert that session_run_index increase monotonically.
1557         session_run_indices = zip(timestamps, session_run_indices)
1558         session_run_indices = sorted(session_run_indices, key=lambda x: x[0])
1559         for i in xrange(len(session_run_indices) - 1):
1560           self.assertGreater(session_run_indices[i + 1][1],
1561                              session_run_indices[i][1])
1562 
1563       # Assert that the session_run_indices from the concurrent run() calls are
1564       # all unique.
1565       self.assertEqual(len(all_session_run_indices),
1566                        len(set(all_session_run_indices)))
1567

1569 if __name__ == "__main__":
1570   googletest.main()
